<subSubSection pageId="214" pageNumber="215" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="214.[136,778,1381,2093]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,258,1381,1407]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species in the group 
<taxonomicName box="[549,650,1381,1407]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[549,650,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are readily recognized by discontinuous thoracic fovea that is interrupted in middle (
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[399,774,1457,1484]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 42 A) and the sternum with a deep central depression (
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[143,502,1533,1560]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 42 B). The resemble all other species of 
<typeStatus box="[351,399,1572,1598]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">type</typeStatus>
II morphology proposed by Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018 (which include most species described here) by triangular shape of the post-labial sigilla, sternal sigilla I–II elongated, and, in females, by the abundant retrolateral thorns on tibia II and by the lobed spermathecae. They resemble 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[569,710,1762,1788]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[569,710,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 107" captionStartId="117.[136,235,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,196,1142]" captionTargetId="figure-395@117.[151,1436,189,1145]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURE 107. Actinopus crassipes (Keyserling, 1891), male: A–C MCN 30740: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral.PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal TegularApophysis; PAc-ProlateralAccessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597460/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 107 A</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" box="[227,437,1800,1826]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[227,437,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[453,574,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 112" captionStartId="124.[136,235,1048,1072]" captionTargetBox="[232,1413,206,1008]" captionTargetId="figure-347@124.[151,1436,189,1024]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 112 A–C. Actinopus dubiomaculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1923, male: A–C MZSP 7636: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597470/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 112 A</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[636,777,1800,1826]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[636,777,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[144,278,1838,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="142.[136,235,1421,1445]" captionTargetBox="[176,1391,200,1372]" captionTargetId="figure-233@142.[151,1435,189,1397]" captionTargetPageId="142" captionText="FIGURE 129. Actinopus laventana sp. nov., male: A–C LZI M135: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D FCE-MY 977: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597508/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 129 A</figureCitation>
), included on group 
<emphasis box="[532,646,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">crassipes¸</emphasis>
by the PA continuous to PI. Females of group 
<taxonomicName box="[549,650,1876,1902]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis box="[549,650,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" box="[136,354,1914,1940]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[136,354,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[377,479,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURE 112" captionStartId="124.[136,235,1048,1072]" captionTargetBox="[232,1413,206,1008]" captionTargetId="figure-347@124.[151,1436,189,1024]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 112 A–C. Actinopus dubiomaculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1923, male: A–C MZSP 7636: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597470/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
D–H) and 
<taxonomicName box="[628,777,1914,1940]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[628,777,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[144,268,1952,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="142.[136,235,1421,1445]" captionTargetBox="[176,1391,200,1372]" captionTargetId="figure-233@142.[151,1435,189,1397]" captionTargetPageId="142" captionText="FIGURE 129. Actinopus laventana sp. nov., male: A–C LZI M135: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D FCE-MY 977: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597508/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 129 D</figureCitation>
) the similar shape of receptacles. They differ from 
<taxonomicName box="[200,344,1990,2017]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis box="[200,344,1990,2017]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of lateral swelling on receptacles.
</paragraph>
